    "department": "Solution Engineering",
    "description": "At Snowflake, we are powering the era of the agentic enterprise. To usher in this new era, we seek AI-native thinkers across every function who are energized by the opportunity to reinvent how they work. You don’t just use tools; you possess an innate curiosity, treating AI as a high-trust collaborator that is core to how you solve problems and accelerate your impact. We look for low-ego individuals who thrive in dynamic and fast-moving environments and move with an experimental mindset — who rapidly test emerging capabilities to discover simpler, more powerful ways to deliver results. At Snowflake, your role isn't just to execute a function, but to help redefine the future of how work gets done.\n\n\nGLOBAL ACCOUNT MANAGER, SOLUTION ENGINEERING\n\nSnowflake is about empowering enterprises to achieve their full potential — and people too. With a culture that’s all in on impact, innovation, and collaboration, Snowflake is the sweet spot for building big, moving fast, and taking technology — and careers — to the next level.\n\nOur Solution Engineering organization is seeking a Global Account Manager (GAM SE) to lead the technical vision for our most strategic global accounts. We are looking for a visionary leader who can architect comprehensive technical strategies while navigating the complexities of a global enterprise ecosystem. In this role, you will be the technical heartbeat of the account, partnering intimately with Global Account Managers to align Snowflake’s Cloud Data Platform with overarching business objectives. You aren’t just a contributor; you are the owner of the global technical roadmap, responsible for driving adoption, mentoring regional SE teams, and ultimately carrying the global account target. You are equally comfortable in a high-stakes boardroom, presenting to CTOs and CIOs, as you are \"talking shop\" with technical architects to solve the world's most complex data challenges.\n\n\nIN THIS ROLE YOU WILL GET TO:\n\n - Architect Global Strategy: Own and execute the end-to-end technical roadmap for Snowflake’s largest global customers, ensuring seamless alignment across every region and subsidiary.\n\n - Drive Massive Impact: Directly influence and carry the global account’s annual target by demonstrating the undeniable value proposition of Snowflake’s evolving technology stack.\n\n - Lead and Mentor: Act as a force multiplier by directly managing or indirectly influencing a global cohort of Solution Engineers, providing the strategic guidance needed to win complex sales cycles.\n\n - Partner at the Summit: Form a formidable leadership duo with the Global Account Manager (GAM), blending technical excellence with commercial strategy to secure and expand Snowflake’s footprint.\n\n - Innovate \u0026 Evangelize: Stay at the forefront of the industry, translating emerging trends into innovative solutions that differentiate Snowflake from the competition.\n\n\nON DAY ONE, WE WILL EXPECT YOU TO HAVE:\n\n - 8+ years of experience in technical sales or solution engineering, with a proven track record of managing large-scale, complex accounts.\n\n - Experience managing direct reports or leading cross-functional technical teams through influence and collaboration.\n\n - Exceptional ability to act as a trusted advisor to C-suite technical stakeholders, translating complex technical roadmaps into business value.\n\n - Mastery of the Snowflake Cloud Data Platform and a broad understanding of the data ecosystem, including Data Lake, Mesh, and AI/ML integration.\n\n - The ability to navigate different regional markets and cultures to ensure a unified technical approach for the client.\n\n - A collaborative spirit that thrives in high-pressure, high-reward environments where technical and commercial success go hand-in-hand.\n\nEvery Snowflake employee is expected to follow the company’s confidentiality and security standards for handling sensitive data. Snowflake employees must abide by the company’s data security plan as an essential part of their duties. It is every employee's duty to keep customer information secure and confidential.\n\nSnowflake is growing fast, and we’re scaling our team to help enable and accelerate our growth. We are looking for people who share our values, challenge ordinary thinking, and push the pace of innovation while building a future for themselves and Snowflake.\n\nHow do you want to make your impact?\n\nFor jobs located in the United States, please visit the job posting on the Snowflake Careers Site for salary and benefits information: careers.snowflake.com http://careers.snowflake.com",
